<div id="review_3326272946" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3326272946" />
    <a title="Santosh Panda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26199602-santosh-panda"><img alt="Santosh Panda" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1592208707p2/26199602.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3326272946?book_show_action=true">May 08, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Santosh Panda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Santosh Panda" href="/user/show/26199602-santosh-panda">Santosh Panda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3326272946" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1601138575205221412">Okay okay, let me be calm before writing this review. For the story, you can check the book&apos;s blurb in the description, I don&apos;t want to bore you. So let me get straight into my review.<br/><br/>Before writing, what I liked about this book, let me tell you what I disliked in this book. Ummmm, there is not a single thing that I can point about disliking this book. This book is definitely one of the best books that I have ever read.<br/><br/>The story is all about the love between Arya and Rudra, and their eternal lov</span>
  <span id="freeText1601138575205221412" style="display:none">Okay okay, let me be calm before writing this review. For the story, you can check the book's blurb in the description, I don't want to bore you. So let me get straight into my review.<br /><br />Before writing, what I liked about this book, let me tell you what I disliked in this book. Ummmm, there is not a single thing that I can point about disliking this book. This book is definitely one of the best books that I have ever read.<br /><br />The story is all about the love between Arya and Rudra, and their eternal love. Can you believe Rudra waited for 10 long years to get back his love again? <br /><br />Though the book has some side plots mainly the story revolves around Arya and Rudra. The author has done a commendable job by simultaneously narrating the stories from the past and present. Not for a single time, I was able to drop the book before completely reading it.<br /><br />Definitely, this book is a page-turner and one can never stop without completing it. Though it ended I craved for more. I was so engrossed in the book that I didn't realize how the time flew by. <br /><br />If you are looking for some Romance genre books and quite new to the world of books, then don't think twice before picking it up. Trust me you won't regret reading this book. <br /><br />Don't remember the last time I had read such a lovely book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1601138575205221412" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


