        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3853099623" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10954647850874541336">Bestowed <br/><br/>Isn&apos;t it a blessing to be Bestowed with finding your soul mate and choosing them for a lifetime of togetherness... <br/><br/>Isn&apos;t it a blessing to be Bestowed with the responsibility to take care of the ones you love.. <br/><br/>Isnt it a blessing to be Bestowed with  blessings of the ones who brought you into this world and want and mean the best for you... <br/><br/>Rudra and Arya is one such couple who realise their love for each other as young children and marry by exchanging the Shafalika garland on an auspici</span>
  <span id="freeText10954647850874541336" style="display:none">Bestowed <br /><br />Isn't it a blessing to be Bestowed with finding your soul mate and choosing them for a lifetime of togetherness... <br /><br />Isn't it a blessing to be Bestowed with the responsibility to take care of the ones you love.. <br /><br />Isnt it a blessing to be Bestowed with  blessings of the ones who brought you into this world and want and mean the best for you... <br /><br />Rudra and Arya is one such couple who realise their love for each other as young children and marry by exchanging the Shafalika garland on an auspicious evening without even knowing the significance of what they've done. But is that all to their marriage...I wish too. The ups and downs and twists and turns only makes their connection deeper and stronger. <br /><br />This simple love story entwined with the complications life can throw, will teleport you to a world where you wish you were part off, wanting to smile and laugh and cry with the characters. <br /><br />An unputdownble book that'll leave you feeling content at the end..<br /><br />Sunandini Jayant</span>
