<div id="review_3183227709" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3183227709" />
    <a title="Nisha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/109929119-nisha"><img alt="Nisha" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3183227709?book_show_action=true">Feb 09, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nisha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nisha" href="/user/show/109929119-nisha">Nisha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3183227709&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3183227709" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7185764705858821126">#RudrArya<br/>This is a story of eternal love. A very few stories touches you like this one. The very first chapter has the gripping affect. As the story unfolds you find yourself entrigued by the suspence and the simplicity with which the author depicts the emotions.<br/>The Sindoor Khela scene is charam. I could visualise the emotions on the faces of the protagonist as is I was there in between them.<br/><br/>Cheers to the author for making us a part of the story.<br/>Keep writing, waiting for more such gripping stori</span>
  <span id="freeText7185764705858821126" style="display:none">#RudrArya<br />This is a story of eternal love. A very few stories touches you like this one. The very first chapter has the gripping affect. As the story unfolds you find yourself entrigued by the suspence and the simplicity with which the author depicts the emotions.<br />The Sindoor Khela scene is charam. I could visualise the emotions on the faces of the protagonist as is I was there in between them.<br /><br />Cheers to the author for making us a part of the story.<br />Keep writing, waiting for more such gripping stories from you.<br /></span>
